Verse: The person said: "Write what you see in a book. You must send the book to the 7 churches in these cities: Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamum, Thyatira, Sardis, Philadelphia, and Laodicea.’
I turned around to see who was speaking to me. When I turned, I saw 7 lights in gold lamps.
In the middle of the lights, I saw a person who looked like a man. He was wearing long clothes that reached down to his feet. And he wore a gold belt around the top half of his body.
His head and his hair were white like sheep's hair. They were very white, like snow. And his eyes were like fires that were burning.
His feet shined like yellow metal that shines brightly in a very hot fire. When he spoke, his voice was like the sound of many rivers. It was like many rivers that were moving very fast.
He held 7 stars in his right hand. And there was a sharp sword with two edges coming out of his mouth. His face was like the sun when it shines very brightly.
When I saw him, I fell down at his feet like a dead person. Then he put his right hand on me. "Do not be afraid', he said to me. "I am first and I am last.
I am God who is alive. I died one time. But look, I am alive. And I will be alive always. And I have the keys to death and Hades.
So write down the things that you have seen. Write about what is happening now. And write about what will happen later.'
"You saw 7 stars in my right hand. You saw 7 lights, in gold lamps. This is what they mean. The 7 stars mean the angels of you 7 churches. And the 7 lights in their lamps mean you 7 churches.'
